<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="162" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[831,1437,1846,2062]" pageId="3" pageNumber="162">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[831,964,1846,1869]" pageId="3" pageNumber="162">Comments:</emphasis>
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1296,1430,1846,1870]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nepalense">
<emphasis box="[1296,1430,1846,1870]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="162">S. nepalense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs by the colour pattern of the elytra and the male sexual characters. Notable are in the new species the thicker tibiae, the metaventrite with long curled setae forming a ridge-like mesal comb, the apical part of the parameres barely widened in lateral view, and the distinctive shape of the sclerites of the internal sac.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
